item.dc:creator: @13om13e12 13om13e12
item.description:
@13om13e12 wrote:

the formula for this problem is

A!/B!*(a-b)!

A being the amount of numbers
B being the amount of slots so
A=9
B=4
the ! refers to all the numbers under it multiplied with it
so the equation now is 987654321/((4321)(54321))
which then equals 362880/2880=126
but what you are talking about i think is permutation not combination. permutation is when order matters and combination it doesnt. in permutation 1234 and 2134 are different. in combination there refered to as the same group.
so for this problem. you just line up the slots and multiply like if it were 9! but only untill you filled the slot
so in this case its 9876 because there are 4 slots. thats a permutation and the ending answer is 3024[br][size=1]Posted at: December 14, 2006, 01:31:36 PM[/size][hr]whops never mind there are 10 numbers forgot about 0 so in this case it would be 1098*7 which add up to 5040 also if you have a TI 82 or higher calculator. (i think its on the TI 82) if you go under math menu and go to the prb tab there is an option for !,ncr,and npr. ncr is combination and npr is permutation. 10 p 4 = 5040
[br][size=1]Posted at: December 14, 2006, 01:36:10 PM[/size][hr]im sorry for posting again but i found out what was wrong with what i said. this equation only works if you could only use the number once in a single group. but if you were to do what you are talking about it would just be every interger uner 10000 or there would be 10000 different possibilities.
